-- TSMC's Chang Forecasts World Chip Market to Expand 5 Percent Next Year
-- B y   T i m   C u l p a n
-- 2010-10-28T06:32:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/tsmc-s-chang-forecasts-world-chip-market-to-expand-5-percent-next-year.html
The global semiconductor market will
likely grow 5 percent next year, Taiwan Semiconductor
Manufacturing Co. Chairman Morris Chang said.  Chang expects the foundry industry to expand by 14 percent,
he said at an investors’ conference in Taipei today.  His company’s sales will likely climb more than 14 percent
in 2011, Chang said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tim Culpan in Taipei at 
